The code should be clean, modular and extensible rather than over-engineered.

Favor maintainability and developer productivity over enterprise features.


Implementation strategy: Build this incrementally in phases. At the end of each phase, the project must compile and be runnable. Prioritize working software over completeness. Do not generate placeholder code. Produce production-quality code for each implemented feature before moving to the next phase.
